### 1. Check if Server is Alive
GET http://127.0.0.1:5000/

### 2. Login (Change credentials to match your code)
POST http://127.0.0.1:5000/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "PLACEHOLDER_EMAIL",
    "password": "PLACEHOLDER_PASSWORD"
}

### 3. Create Article
POST http://127.0.0.1:5000/articles
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "My Test Event",
    "type": "Event",
    "author": "Backend Dev",
    "content": "This is a test content.",
    "tags": ["Testing"]
}

### 4. Get All Articles
GET http://127.0.0.1:5000/articles

### 5. Update Article (Replace '1' with actual ID from step 4)
PUT http://127.0.0.1:5000/articles/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "title": "UPDATED TITLE",
    "type": "Event",
    "author": "Backend Dev",
    "content": "Content updated.",
    "tags": ["Updated"]
}
